<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Incredible room and Incredible price...We love this place In the past 6 months, my husband and I have stayed in this hotel at least 4 times, and each time we love it more. This is one of the only places we like to stay. We also stayed here prior to September 11th, so it holds a special place in our heart. For those of you who can't handle the memories of 9-11, you probably shouldn't stay here since it is directly across the street. If you get a room in the front of the hotel you WILL be overlooking ground zero through your large hotel room window. As sad as it is for us, we actually feel a connection staying here so often. The hotel was actually damaged (the building is all glass) and many of the windows were shattered. It just reopened in May, 2003. All I can say is this must be the VERY BEST buy in NYC. Their are only a couple of things I can see someone complaining about. First, if you are only interested in staying somewhere that has tons to do around you, this isn't the place. It is located in the Wall St. Financial district which is kind of dull on the weekends. For us, that doesn't matter since it is very close to the Village and Soho and we also have our car with us and don't mind driving 10 minutes. You will find stores and restaurants, but it isn't hustle and bustle like you find in many other areas. THE ROOM. This room is great! For NYC I would say this is very big. It is decorated modern, extremely clean, nice bathrooms with marble and granite, the 2nd most Comfortable hotel bed we have ever slept on (the Westin has the heavenly bed which is a tiny bit better), and an AMAZING 42 plasma TV built into the wall right in front of your bed....It is truly incredible, and for the prices you can usually get a king room for, I can't imagine anything is better in NYC. (when we book on internet travel sights ie: hotels.com, orbitz.com, etc) we have gotten the king deluxe rooms for as low as 136.00 a night to 160.00 a night. The hotel staff are so friendly and the elevators are nice and fast. I can't speak for the food since we have never eaten here. You will really like this hotel.....I feel completely comfortable recommending it to anyone visiting NYC. 
